          :markdown
            This is a demo of the form fields for The Knot as designed by
            Silvia Tueros-Cossio. It was patternized and turned into this
            demo (and corresponding [repo](https://github.com/xogroup/tk-form-fields)
            by [Marco Carag](https://github.com/jazzcrazed)).

          h2
            a#usage Usage

          :markdown

            1. Download **[tk-form-fields.0.0.2.css](https://github.com/xogroup/tk-form-fields/blob/master/bin/tk-form-fields.0.0.2.css)**.
            2. Place the file somewhere in your application that makes sense.
              a. In Rails, `vendor/assets` would probably make sense.
              b. In an Express Node app, try serving out of `vendor` -- eg:
                 ```
                 app.use('/static', express.static(__dirname + '/vendor'));
                 ```
            3. Then architect your form's markup, following the below demo as an example. So long as you're using the appropriate classes and HTML, all should be well!

      .row
        .col-md-4.col-md-offset-4
          h2
            a#demo Demo
          form.tk-form-fields(action='#0')
            fieldset.row
              .col-xs-6
                input#first_name(type='text', name='first_name', required='', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='first_name') First Name
              .col-xs-6
                input#last_name(type='text', name='last_name', required='', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='last_name') Last Name
            .row
              fieldset.col-xs-12
                input#nickname(type='text', name='nickname', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='nickname') Nickname
            .row
              fieldset.col-xs-12
                input#email(type='email', name='email', required='', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='email') Email Address
                .requirements
                  | Must be a valid email address.
            .row
              fieldset.col-xs-12
                input#password(type='password', name='password', required='', placeholder=' ', pattern='(?=.*\d)(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z]).{6,}')
                label(for='password') Password
                .requirements
                  | Your password must be at least 6 characters as well as contain at least one uppercase, one lowercase, and one number.
            .row
              fieldset.col-xs-12
                input#tel(type='tel', name='tel', required='', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='tel') Phone Number
            .row
              fieldset.col-xs-12
                input#guest_count(type='number', name='guest_count', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='guest_count') Guest Count
            .row
              fieldset.col-xs-12
                input#ww_url(type='url', name='ww_url', required='', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='ww_url') Wedding Website URL
            .row
              fieldset.col-xs-12
                input#hint(type='text', name='hint', disabled='', placeholder=' ')
                label(for='nickname') Hint
            .row
              fieldset.textarea-container.col-xs-12
                label(for='optional') Optional
                textarea#optional(rows='5', name='optional', placeholder='Example note: Hi! Thank you so much for inviting us to your wedding. See you soon!')
            .row
              fieldset.textarea-container.col-xs-12
                textarea#optional_2(rows='5', name='optional_2', placeholder='Another really long note.')
            .row
              .col-xs-12
                button.btn-block(type='submit') Sign Up
                button.btn-block(disabled='true') Disabled button
      .row
        .col-md-4.col-md-offset-4
          h2
            a#contributing Contributing changes

          :markdown
            **DO NOT modify the `tk-form-fields.0.0.4.css` directly!!!** Instead,
            fork the [repo](https://github.com/xogroup/tk-form-fields), make your
            changes there, and file a pull request. You could also file an
            [issue](https://github.com/xogroup/tk-form-fields/issues)

            If you need to change things more urgently, override the css/html
            in your application's stylesheets and templates (eg, in a Rails app
            within `app/assets/application.css`).
